PCA implementation

author: Guochen Dai

For a corrleated 2D dataset

library(MASS)
X<- mvrnorm(n = 500, c(2,6), matrix(c(1.2,1.1,1.1,1.2),nrow=2), tol = 1e-6, empirical = FALSE, EISPACK = FALSE)
x<- X[,1]-mean(X[,1])
y<- X[,2]-mean(X[,2])
plot(x,y,type="p",cex=0.5,col="darkgreen",asp=1)
arrows(0,0,1,0,col="darkred",length = 0.1,lwd=3)
arrows(0,0,0,1,col="darkred",length = 0.1,lwd=3)
grid()

X<- cbind(x,y)
new_axis = eigen(1/nrow(X)*t(X)%*%X)$vectors
new_var = eigen(1/nrow(X)*t(X)%*%X)$values
plot(x,y,type="p",cex=0.5,col="darkgreen",asp=1)
arrows(0,0,1,0,col="darkred",length = 0.1,lwd=3)
arrows(0,0,0,1,col="darkred",length = 0.1,lwd=3)
arrows(0,0,new_axis[1,1],new_axis[2,1],col="pink",length = 0.1,lwd=3)
arrows(0,0,new_axis[1,2],new_axis[2,2],col="pink",length = 0.1,lwd=3)
grid()

under new axis:

new_X<- X%*%new_axis
plot(new_X,type="p",cex=0.5,col="darkgreen",xlab="x'",ylab="y'",asp=1)
arrows(0,0,1,0,col="darkred",length = 0.1,lwd=3)
arrows(0,0,0,1,col="darkred",length = 0.1,lwd=3)
grid()

Next we extend to 3D

library(scatterplot3d)
X<- mvrnorm(n = 500, c(2,6,9), matrix(c(1.2,1.1,-0.8,1.1,1.2,-0.9,-0.8,-0.9,1.2),nrow=3), tol = 1e-6, empirical = FALSE, EISPACK = FALSE)
x<- X[,1]-mean(X[,1])
y<- X[,2]-mean(X[,2])
z<- X[,3]-mean(X[,3])
p3d<- scatterplot3d(x,y,z,scale.y = 1,highlight.3d = T,pch=20)
p3d$plane3d(0,0,0,lty="dotted")

This is the plot under new basis:

X<- cbind(x,y,z)
new_axis = eigen(1/nrow(X)*t(X)%*%X)$vectors
new_var = eigen(1/nrow(X)*t(X)%*%X)$values
new_X<- X%*%new_axis
p3d<- scatterplot3d(new_X[,1],new_X[,2],new_X[,3],xlab="x'",ylab="y'",zlab="z'",highlight.3d = T,scale.y = 1,pch=20)
p3d$plane3d(0,0,0,lty="dotted")

Get the variance proportion explained by three components.

barplot(new_var/sum(new_var),names.arg=paste("PC",1:3))

Move to financial market, get data first

library(quantmod)
get_stock_ret_pca<- function(start,end){
  tickers<- c("SPY","AAPL","QQQ","T","IWM","DOW")
  ret_matrix<- NULL
  for (i in 1:length(tickers)){
    temp<- getSymbols(tickers[i],src = "google",from= start,to =end,auto.assign = F)
    temp<- na.omit(log(temp[,4]/lag(temp[,4])))
    # mean 0
    temp<- temp-mean(temp)
    ret_matrix<- cbind(ret_matrix,temp)
  }
  return(ret_matrix)
}

pca

start = "2015-01-01"
end = "2016-01-01"
ret_matrix<- get_stock_ret_pca(start,end)
new_var<- eigen(1/nrow(ret_matrix)*t(ret_matrix)%*%ret_matrix)$values
barplot(new_var/sum(new_var),names.arg=paste("PC",1:length(new_var)),
        main="PCA of mean adjusted stock returns",
        sub=paste("(",start,"~",end,") 1st PC=",round((new_var/sum(new_var))[1],2),"and",
          length(new_var[cumsum(new_var/sum(new_var))<=0.9])+1,"PC>=90%"))

start = "2008-9-01"
end = "2009-1-1"
ret_matrix<- get_stock_ret_pca(start,end)
new_var<- eigen(1/nrow(ret_matrix)*t(ret_matrix)%*%ret_matrix)$values
barplot(new_var/sum(new_var),names.arg=paste("PC",1:length(new_var)),
        main="PCA of mean adjusted stock returns",
        sub=paste("(",start,"~",end,") 1st PC=",round((new_var/sum(new_var))[1],2),"and",
                  length(new_var[cumsum(new_var/sum(new_var))<=0.9])+1,"PC>=90%"))
